        "findus": "You can also find us at",
        "MeladoInfo": "El Melado is a picturesque town located in the commune of Colbún, in the region of Maule, Chile. This place stands out for its natural environment, surrounded by mountains, rivers and lush vegetation, making it an ideal destination for nature lovers and ecotourism. El Melado is known for the reservoir of the same name, an impressive engineering work that supplies water to the area and is used for hydroelectric power generation. In addition, its landscapes are perfect for activities such as hiking, fishing and the sighting of native flora and fauna, offering a unique experience in contact with the tranquility of the mountain range.",
        "PehuencheInfo": "Paso Pehuenche, located in the Maule Region, Chile, is a mountain pass that connects the country with Argentina, offering a breathtaking route through the Andes Mountains. This pass is known for its spectacular scenery, which varies from vast plains to towering rock formations and snow-capped peaks. During the journey, visitors can enjoy panoramic views that highlight the majesty of the Andes and the diversity of local flora and fauna. In winter, the pass can be covered by a layer of snow, which adds a magical touch to the environment. Its relevance lies not only in its natural beauty, but also in its importance as a key route for commercial and cultural exchange between Chile and Argentina.",
        "ColbunInfo": "Colbún is the capital of the commune, acting as an administrative and commercial center. In this town is concentrated a large number of services such as the municipality, health center, bank, among others. In addition, it also has a great variety of commerce, supermarkets, stores, pharmacies, restaurants, where you can satisfy all your needs. In this place, you can also find a tourist office to inform you of all the attractions of the commune and other must-see places to visit.",
        "GuardiaInfo": "Along the road to Lake Colbún you reach La Guardia, in the midst of pine trees and a natural landscape that invites you to walk through it is this small town. It is known for being the home of the Chancho al Humo activity that takes place in August and celebrates the typical customs of the sector.",
        "BoldosInfo": "Los Boldos is a picturesque town in the commune of Colbún, located in the Maule region of Chile. This charming corner stands out for its wide natural spaces and serene surroundings, characterized by green hills and rich biodiversity. Los Boldos is known for its proximity to the Colbún reservoir, which offers opportunities for recreational activities such as boating and fishing. In addition, the area is ideal for those looking to explore nature through hikes and trails through breathtaking landscapes. With its tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, Los Boldos provides an authentic and relaxing experience in the heart of central Chile, where the local community lives in harmony with the environment.",
        "PanimavidaInfo": "Panimávida is a picturesque town in the commune of Colbún, located in the Maule region of Chile. Famous for its natural hot springs, Panimávida offers a haven of relaxation and wellness in the midst of a stunning natural environment. Panimávida's mineral-rich hot springs provide a rejuvenating experience while you are surrounded by landscapes of green hills and the serenity of the region. In addition, the area is ideal for those looking to explore nature through trails and enjoy outdoor activities at the nearby Colbún reservoir. With its combination of natural beauty and healing properties, Panimávida invites visitors to immerse themselves in a unique experience of rest and connection with nature in the heart of Maule.",
        "RariInfo": "Rari is a charming town in the commune of Colbún, in the Maule region of Chile, known for its rich artisan tradition. This picturesque place stands out for its craftswomen who preserve and transmit ancestral techniques in the elaboration of textiles, basketry and ceramics, creating unique pieces that reflect the essence of the local culture. Rari's handcrafted products are appreciated for their quality and care in every detail, combining traditional materials with innovative designs. By visiting Rari, you can get an up-close look at the process of creating these works of art, interact with the talented artisans and acquire authentic souvenirs that capture the spirit and tradition of the region. The Rari experience offers an immersion into the cultural heritage of Colbún, where the skill and passion of its artisans transform tradition into living art.",
        "QuinamavidaInfo": "Quinamávida is a charming town in the commune of Colbún, in the Maule region of Chile, known for its rich artisan tradition. Here, local artisans preserve and transmit ancestral techniques in the creation of textiles and handmade products that reflect the cultural richness and ingenuity of the region. Each piece made in Quinamávida is a testimony to the talent and dedication of its creators, who use traditional materials and traditional methods to offer unique and high quality products. By visiting Quinamávida, you can explore the artisans' workshops, learn about the process behind each creation and acquire authentic souvenirs that capture the spirit of the region. The Quinamávida experience offers an immersion in local art and tradition, combining the beauty of its landscapes with the richness of its cultural heritage.",
        "RabonesInfo": "Rabones is a picturesque town in the commune of Colbún, in the Maule region of Chile, which stands out for its peaceful rural setting and stunning natural scenery. Surrounded by green hills and bathed by the Colbún River, this area offers a serene atmosphere and close contact with nature. In Rabones, visitors can enjoy outdoor activities such as hiking and biking, exploring the scenic beauty of the region. The local community, known for its warmth and hospitality, contributes to create a welcoming and authentic atmosphere. Rabones is the ideal place for those seeking a quiet getaway in the heart of Maule, immersed in the serenity and charm of Chile's rural landscapes.",
        "BellotosInfo": "Los Bellotos is a picturesque village in the commune of Colbún, in the Maule region of Chile, known for its serene atmosphere and stunning natural surroundings. Located in an area of green hills and rich vegetation, Los Bellotos offers an authentic experience of rural Chilean life. The area is noted for its tranquil landscapes and its proximity to the Colbún reservoir, which provides opportunities to enjoy outdoor recreational activities such as fishing and boating. The warm and welcoming local community contributes to the charm of the place, offering an immersion in the country life and natural beauty of the heart of the Maule region. Los Bellotos is the ideal destination for those seeking to escape the urban bustle and immerse themselves in the serenity and splendor of Chilean nature.",
        "BalneariosInfo": "Balneario Machicura, located in Colbún, Chile, is an outstanding destination for those seeking to enjoy natural beauty and tranquility in the heart of the Maule region. This charming seaside resort, located on the banks of the Machicura Reservoir, offers a serene setting surrounded by green hills and picturesque landscapes. Here, visitors can enjoy a variety of outdoor activities, such as swimming in the crystal-clear waters of the reservoir, practicing water sports or simply relaxing by the beach. With its cozy atmosphere and stunning natural surroundings, the Machicura Spa is the ideal place to escape the urban bustle and immerse oneself in a revitalizing experience in nature.",
